HEADWORD: Pearlstone
<hw>Pearl"stone`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A glassy
volcanic rock of a grayish color and pearly luster, often having a
spherulitic concretionary structure due to the curved cracks produced by
contraction in cooling. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Perlitic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pearlwort</ent>⟦br⟧
